    <text id="A6236T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>William Evans writes his brother David and discusses business and civic life in
                    Staunton and Winchester, and gives family news.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-10">Nov. 10 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Bro</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I was truly glad to <orig reg="hear">here</orig> from You. You Must pardon Me for
                    delaying so long. I would of answered Sooner but My time is so Much taken up
                    that I put it <orig reg="off">of</orig> from time to time <orig reg="until"
                        >untill</orig> four weeks has Elapsed Since your Much Esteemed
                        <unclear>letter</unclear> come to hand. You Speak Well for Staunton She is
                    far ahead of our town in Schools I <orig reg="don't">dont</orig> think there is
                    a first class school in Our town at this time</p>

                <pb n="2"/>
                <p>but I suppose Some Gentlemen With literary taste will establish One-- You also
                    pay quite a compliment to the people of Winchester in Speaking of their Business
                    qualifications I think My Self business is conducted <orig reg="different"
                        >differant</orig> in Winchester from what it is in Staunton but <orig
                        reg="whether">whethe</orig> it is conducted to a greater advantage I <orig
                        reg="can't">cant</orig> tell-- as the people Seems to prosper in business up
                    there as well as Winchester. I am sorry to inform you that Mother has been very
                    sick I really thought she would not recover but she <pb n="3"/>is getting
                    better. I hope she will recover her health again.</p>

                <p>Tif arrived from Moorefield on yesterday she is well but is talking of going back
                    again in a couple of weeks All the family are well you Must write soon again.
                    Love to all</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Bro</salute>
                    <signed>Wm. L. Evans</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
